In this article, President Trump discusses the recent incident in the Strait of Hormuz involving the USS Boxer and an Iranian drone. He emphasizes the United States' right to defend its personnel and calls on other nations to condemn Iran's actions. Trump also welcomes Prime Minister Mark Rutte of the Netherlands and several World War Two veterans to the White House. He receives an American flag that flew during the D-Day invasion and thanks the donors from the Netherlands who purchased the flag and returned it as a gift to the United States. The flag will be displayed at the Smithsonian's Museum of American History. Trump concludes by introducing Prime Minister Rutte, who will speak about the treasured gift.